                  <p>It’s a unique experiential learning initiative where students participate in Himalayan treks, adventure camps, and outdoor challenges. The goal is to develop leadership, teamwork, resilience, and environmental awareness while ensuring safety and fun.</p>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
               <div class="faq-question">
                  <span>Who can join the program?</span>
                  <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
               </div>
               <div class="faq-answer">
                  <p>
                     <strong>Level 1 (Classes 1–4):</strong> Fun campus-based adventure activities.<br>
                     <strong>Level 2 (Classes 5–8):</strong> Overnight Himalayan adventure camps with fixed camping.<br>
                     <strong>Level 3 (Classes 9–12):</strong> Multi-day high-altitude Himalayan treks with leadership and survival training.
                  </p>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
               <div class="faq-question">
                  <span>Is it safe for children to trek in the Himalayas?</span>
                  <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
               </div>
               <div class="faq-answer">
                  <ul>
                     <li>✅ Certified trek leaders trained at NIM, HMI, ABVIMAS, NOLS</li>
                     <li>✅ Daily health monitoring (BP & oxygen levels)</li>
                     <li>✅ Emergency backup plans and medical support</li>
                     <li>✅ High-quality, age-appropriate gear</li>
                     <li>✅ Carefully designed itineraries with acclimatization days</li>
                  </ul>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
               <div class="faq-question">
                  <span>What kind of skills will students learn?</span>
                  <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
               </div>
               <div class="faq-answer">
                  <ul>
                     <li>Leadership & teamwork</li>
                     <li>Problem-solving & decision-making</li>
                     <li>First Aid, CPR, and survival basics</li>
                     <li>Disaster management & sustainability practices</li>
                     <li>Confidence, independence, and resilience</li>
                  </ul>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
               <div class="faq-question">
                  <span>Do students need prior trekking experience?</span>
                  <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
               </div>
               <div class="faq-answer">
                  <p>No 👌 Beginners are welcome. Our programs are designed for all fitness levels, with proper guidance and gradual exposure to trekking. Students only need enthusiasm and a willingness to learn.</p>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
         <!-- Right Column -->
         <div class="faq-column" data-group="right">
            <div class="faq-item">
               <div class="faq-question">
                  <span>What kind of food and accommodation is provided?</span>
                  <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
               </div>
               <div class="faq-answer">
                  <ul>
                     <li>🍲 Meals: Nutritious, balanced meals designed to keep students energized.</li>
                     <li>⛺ Stay: Safe camping in tents or designated campsites, with proper sleeping bags and gear.</li>
                     <li>💧 Water: Clean drinking water provided throughout the trek.</li>
                  </ul>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
               <div class="faq-question">
                  <span>How long are the programs?</span>
                  <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
               </div>
               <div class="faq-answer">
                  <p>
                     <strong>Level 1:</strong> Half-day to full-day (school campus).<br>
                     <strong>Level 2:</strong> 2–3 days with overnight camping.<br>
                     <strong>Level 3:</strong> 5–10 days multi-day Himalayan trek (customizable based on school requirements).
                  </p>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
               <div class="faq-question">
                  <span>How do you handle medical emergencies?</span>
                  <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
               </div>
               <div class="faq-answer">
                  <ul>
                     <li>🩺 All leaders are trained in Wilderness First Aid & CPR</li>
                     <li>🧰 We carry first aid kits, oxygen cylinders, and rescue equipment</li>
                     <li>📡 Emergency evacuation procedures and communication systems are always in place</li>
                  </ul>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
               <div class="faq-question">
                  <span>How do parents stay updated during the trek?</span>
                  <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
               </div>
               <div class="faq-answer">
                  <p>
                     We maintain regular communication with schools. Parents receive updates about progress, student well-being, and any special highlights during the trek.
                  </p>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
               <div class="faq-question">
                  <span>How can schools and colleges collaborate?</span>
                  <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
               </div>
               <div class="faq-answer">
                  <p>
                     Institutions can contact Himalayan Hikers directly to customize itineraries based on student age, curriculum goals, and program duration. We handle planning, logistics, safety, and training.
                  </p>
               </div>
